Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.60,0:02:03.92,DefaultItalics,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,A band performance application...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.92,0:02:05.37,DefaultItalics,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,Kessoku Band...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.37,0:02:08.01,DefaultItalics,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,Who wrote all this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.01,0:02:10.86,DefaultItalics,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,What? Hitori Gotoh wrote it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.86,0:02:12.59,DefaultItalics,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a professional guitarist now!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.59,0:02:14.62,DefaultItalics,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,Begone, lust for culture festival attention!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.62,0:02:15.86,DefaultItalics,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,Focus on your band's career!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.79,0:02:21.12,DefaultItalics,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,Good... the lust is fading.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.37,0:02:22.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.78,0:02:27.00,Default,SC President,0000,0000,0000,,Teacher! Someone's collapsed out here!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.85,0:02:42.44,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,I liked dark, cramped spaces,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.44,0:02:44.81,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,so I'd bury my face deep in my hood
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.81,0:02:47.19,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,My eyes resented the heartless world,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.19,0:02:50.94,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,but yearned for love
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.86,0:02:57.58,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,I liked being soaked by the rain,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.58,0:02:59.95,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,because my face looked better clouded over
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.95,0:03:02.59,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,I pretended to be afraid of the storm
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.59,0:03:05.42,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,while waiting for the sky to burst
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.53,0:03:12.38,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,Strum through the light's distortion
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.38,0:03:16.80,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to make thunder roar
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.80,0:03:22.60,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,Drum beyond the pain
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.60,0:03:26.73,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,What can I do? This fierce \Npounding is out of control
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.73,0:03:32.79,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,Strum in a harmonizing quartet
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.79,0:03:36.78,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to cause a revolution
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.78,0:03:42.79,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,Drum in a lamenting forte
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.79,0:03:47.54,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,What can I do? My savage \Nnature is beyond wild
